com.analog.lyric.dimple.factorfunctions

Class ComplexAbs

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.analog.lyric.dimple.factorfunctions.core.FactorFunction
      • com.analog.lyric.dimple.factorfunctions.ComplexAbs
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFactorFunction

    public class ComplexAbs
extends FactorFunction
    Deterministic absolute value of a complex variable. This is a deterministic directed factor (if smoothing is not enabled). Optional smoothing may be applied, by providing a smoothing value in the constructor. If smoothing is enabled, the distribution is smoothed by exp(-difference^2/smoothing), where difference is the distance between the output value and the deterministic output value for the corresponding inputs. The variables are ordered as follows in the argument list: 1) Output (absolute value of the complex input) (Real) 2) Input (Complex)

    0.07
